In ergodic theory, there is a well-known set of isomorphisms and correspondances
 between one dimensional spin lattice models (such as the Ising model or
 Potts model), subshifts of finite type, and motion on hyperbolic surfaces.
 See, for example, 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \cite{May91}

\end_inset 

 for a review.
 This section reviews a small portion of this theory in a simplified manner,
 applying it in a concrete fashion to the question mark function.
\layout Standard

The basic conjecture that is advanced in this section is that multi-fractal
 measures, of which the derivative of the Minkowski question mark is one,
 correspond to smooth and differentiable Hamiltonians, when considered as
 functions under the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

natural
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

