The Kac model and the Question mark function
\layout Standard

The description of the Kac model is similar to that for the Ising model,
 with the exception that the interaction potential is not limited to a nearest
 neighbor interaction, but instead extends between distant sites, with a
 geometrically decreasing strength.
 That is, the potential is given by 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
V(\sigma)=-J(1-\lambda)\,\sigma_{0}\,\sum_{k=1}^{N}\sigma_{k}\lambda^{k}\label{eq:Kac potential}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset 

 a real number determining the strength of the interaction.
 
